At first glance some peeps may think it's a rags to riches tale but so far I don't see much riches involved which is cool<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . I have a few questions tho. You say &quot;Eric&quot; calls Roc up a few weeks later? I was gonna ask where he get's the money to call him but since you're looking for ideas I thought well, he could phone Roc up and Roc'll be like &quot;Thought you were dirt poor kid? How'd you find the money to make a call&quot;. Eric would reply sarcastically &quot;Just cuz I gave you back your wallet, don't mean I gave you all the money in it. A guy's gotta make a living right?&quot;. I was wondering if all these events would take place in like a single issue seeing as quite alot is going on there. I assume Eric starts attending school after he starts living with Roc? You'll probably need to give Eric a lil more background cos I'm wondering where his family is, parents, cousins, grandparents? etc. Of course the simple answer would be orphaned but that's been done and dusted over and over so maybe he needs a new edge. Abusive parents? Family problems? Wanting to get out on his own? Heck, maybe he could have a fine family and all that and is just pulling the wool over Roc's blinkers. Could be a scam he's run on peeps several times to get a bit of dough in his pocket but then realizes there's something different with Roc and he's being offered all sorts of new opportunities he never saw before in his life. So therefore, he'd have the added pressure of trying to hide this fact from Roc. Question is how do you hide the fact that you have a family looking for you? Placing them in a different city would be one idea. But again, this is just an idea for his background. Also, how old is he when the story begins? I dunno much about the US education system but I assume being at highschool he's between 15 and 17 right? <br>
<br>
Also, the guy needs some life away from boxing seeing as that seems to be what's mostly mentioned. Is he gonna make any friends at highschool, maybe meet a girl? And I'm sure they'd be repurcussions from his fight with Zack. (Sorry all my ideas are a little all over place but I'm kinda freestyling it as I go along). By the way, what's Eric's ethic origin? Heck, what's all the characters ethic origin? Whilst it may not matter too much, it would make for some interesting developments. <br>
